{"aid": "40199061", "title": "Surveilr: A Powerful Tool for Resource Surveillance", "url": "https://docs.opsfolio.com/surveilr/", "domain": "opsfolio.com", "votes": 1, "user": "balikilva", "posted_at": "2024-04-29 14:50:36", "comments": 0, "source_title": "Surveilr", "source_text": "Surveilr | Opsfolio Docs\n\nSkip to content\n\nOpsfolio Docs\n\nGitHub Discord\n\n# Surveilr\n\nsurveilr is an extendable file system inspector for performing surveillance of\nmachine resources. It is used to walk resources like file systems and generate\nan SQLite database which can then be consumed by any computing environment\nthat supports SQLite.\n\nThe SQLite file which surveilr prepares is called the Resource Surveillance\nState Database (RSSD) and once it\u2019s been generated it\u2019s no longer tied to\nsurveilr and can be used by any other tool, service, application, or ETL\u2019d\ninto a data warehouse.\n\n", "frontpage": false}
